title: Grateful Dead Live at The Omni on 1994-04-01
description:
Set 1

Picasso Moon-> Deal, Wang Dang Doodle, Dire Wolf, Black Throated Wind*, Bird Song

Set 2

China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Box Of Rain, Estimated Prophet-> He's Gone-> That Would Be Something-> Drums-> Space-> The Other One-> Wharf Rat-> Turn On Your Love Light, E: Brokedown Palace

* Weir on acoustic

reviews.review_text:
I am on an amazing journey I am listening to every 1994 show in order, mining for gold. 

Set 1:

We almost get a top-tier Picasso Moon, until the wheels come off the tracks. Deal in the #2 song slot like on 3/18. Great vocals from Vince. Dire Wolf with trumpet MIDI? Black-Throated Wind was not as good as it was in the Nassau run. Bird Song is dec. I'm still liking 3/30 as the best first set from this run.

Set 2:

This set delivers the goods. Listen from beginning to end. This would be great to pair with 3/30's set 1. VERY respectable China>Rider followed by a killer Box of Rain; Phil just nails it. He's Gone is a Jerry bust-out moment, but not super amazing. That Would Be Something only played 16 times. Drums>Space is worth the spin. 30 mins of headinesss, and one of the better performances thus far in '94, right up there with 3/5. Other One gets interesting. Sweet, sweet Brokedown to close it out.
